Pre-Game Insights: Dawid Malan's displays have been the silver lining of an otherwise miserable England campaign.
Bas de Leede has impressed far more with the ball than he has with the bat.
Joe Root has managed a meagre 188 runs in seven innings, with an average of 26.

Logan van Beek's ten wickets are second to only Bas de Leede for the Netherlands, but he did bowl crucial spells against giants Australia and South Africa, the latter helping the Dutch record a massive upset.
Sybrand Engelbrecht has been significant for the Netherlands' batting efforts, racking up 222 runs in six innings with an average score of 37 and a high score of 70.
